        "content": "1\t# PostHog Laravel Example Project\n2\t\n3\tRepository: https://github.com/PostHog/context-mill\n4\tPath: example-apps/laravel\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## README.md\n9\t\n10\t# PostHog Laravel Example\n11\t\n12\tA Laravel application demonstrating PostHog integration for analytics, feature flags, and error tracking using Livewire for reactive UI components.\n13\t\n14\t## Features\n15\t\n16\t- User registration and authentication with Livewire\n17\t- SQLite database persistence with Eloquent ORM\n18\t- User identification and property tracking\n19\t- Custom event tracking (burrito consideration tracker)\n20\t- Page view tracking (dashboard, profile)\n21\t- Feature flags with payload support\n22\t- Error tracking with manual exception capture\n23\t- Reactive UI components with Livewire\n24\t\n25\t## Tech Stack\n26\t\n27\t- **Framework**: Laravel 11.x\n28\t- **Reactive Components**: Livewire 3.x\n29\t- **Database**: SQLite\n30\t- **Analytics**: PostHog PHP SDK\n31\t\n32\t## Quick Start\n33\t\n34\t**Note**: This is a minimal implementation demonstrating PostHog integration. For a production application, you would need to install Laravel via Composer and set up additional dependencies.\n35\t\n36\t### Manual Setup (Demonstration)\n37\t\n38\t1. Install dependencies:\n39\t   ```bash\n40\t   composer install\n41\t   ```\n42\t\n43\t2. Set up environment:\n44\t   ```bash\n45\t   cp .env.example .env\n46\t   # Edit .env with your PostHog project token\n47\t   ```\n48\t\n49\t3. Configure PostHog in `.env`:\n50\t   ```env\n51\t   POSTHOG_PROJECT_TOKEN=your_posthog_project_token\n52\t   POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com\n53\t   POSTHOG_DISABLED=false\n54\t   ```\n55\t\n56\t4. Generate application key:\n57\t   ```bash\n58\t   php artisan key:generate\n59\t   ```\n60\t\n61\t5. Create database and run migrations:\n62\t   ```bash\n63\t   touch database/database.sqlite\n64\t   php artisan migrate --seed\n65\t   ```\n66\t\n67\t6. Start the development server:\n68\t   ```bash\n69\t   php artisan serve\n70\t   ```\n71\t\n72\t7. Open http://localhost:8000 and either:\n73\t   - Login with default credentials: `admin@example.com` / `admin`\n74\t   - Or click \"Sign up here\" to create a new account\n75\t\n76\t## PostHog Service\n77\t\n78\tThe `PostHogService` class (`app/Services/PostHogService.php`) wraps the PostHog PHP SDK and provides:\n79\t\n80\t| Method | Description |\n81\t|--------|-------------|\n82\t| `identify($distinctId, $properties)` | Identify a user with properties |\n83\t| `capture($distinctId, $event, $properties)` | Capture custom events |\n84\t| `captureException($exception, $distinctId)` | Capture exceptions with stack traces |\n85\t| `isFeatureEnabled($key, $distinctId, $properties)` | Check feature flag status |\n86\t| `getFeatureFlagPayload($key, $distinctId)` | Get feature flag payload |\n87\t\n88\tAll methods check `config('posthog.disabled')` and return early if PostHog is disabled.\n89\t\n90\t## PostHog Integration Points\n91\t\n92\t### User Registration (`app/Http/Livewire/Auth/Register.php`)\n93\tNew users are identified and tracked on signup:\n94\t```php\n95\t$posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n96\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'user_signed_up', [\n97\t    'signup_method' => 'form',\n98\t]);\n99\t```\n100\t\n101\t### User Login (`app/Http/Livewire/Auth/Login.php`)\n102\tUsers are identified on login with their properties:\n103\t```php\n104\t$posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n105\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'user_logged_in', [\n106\t    'login_method' => 'password',\n107\t]);\n108\t```\n109\t\n110\t### User Logout (`routes/web.php`)\n111\tLogout events are tracked:\n112\t```php\n113\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'user_logged_out');\n114\t```\n115\t\n116\t### Page View Tracking\n117\tDashboard and profile views are tracked (`app/Http/Livewire/Dashboard.php`, `app/Http/Livewire/Profile.php`):\n118\t```php\n119\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'dashboard_viewed', [\n120\t    'is_staff' => $user->is_staff,\n121\t]);\n122\t\n123\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'profile_viewed');\n124\t```\n125\t\n126\t### Custom Event Tracking (`app/Http/Livewire/BurritoTracker.php`)\n127\tThe burrito tracker demonstrates custom event capture:\n128\t```php\n129\t$posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n130\t$posthog->capture($user->email, 'burrito_considered', [\n131\t    'total_considerations' => $this->burritoCount,\n132\t]);\n133\t```\n134\t\n135\t### Feature Flags (`app/Http/Livewire/Dashboard.php`)\n136\tThe dashboard demonstrates feature flag checking:\n137\t```php\n138\t$this->showNewFeature = $posthog->isFeatureEnabled(\n139\t    'new-dashboard-feature',\n140\t    $user->email,\n141\t    $user->getPostHogProperties()\n142\t) ?? false;\n143\t\n144\t$this->featureConfig = $posthog->getFeatureFlagPayload(\n145\t    'new-dashboard-feature',\n146\t    $user->email\n147\t);\n148\t```\n149\t\n150\t### Error Tracking\n151\tManual exception capture is demonstrated in multiple places:\n152\t\n153\t**Livewire Components** (`app/Http/Livewire/Dashboard.php`, `app/Http/Livewire/Profile.php`):\n154\t```php\n155\ttry {\n156\t    throw new \\Exception('This is a test error for PostHog tracking');\n157\t} catch (\\Exception $e) {\n158\t    $errorId = $posthog->captureException($e, $user->email);\n159\t    $this->successMessage = \"Error captured in PostHog! Error ID: {$errorId}\";\n160\t}\n161\t```\n162\t\n163\t**API Endpoint** (`app/Http/Controllers/Api/ErrorTestController.php`):\n164\t```php\n165\ttry {\n166\t    throw new \\Exception('Test exception from critical operation');\n167\t} catch (\\Throwable $e) {\n168\t    if ($shouldCapture) {\n169\t        $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n170\t        $eventId = $posthog->captureException($e, $user->email);\n171\t\n172\t        return response()->json([\n173\t            'error' => 'Operation failed',\n174\t            'error_id' => $eventId,\n175\t            'message' => \"Error captured in PostHog. Reference ID: {$eventId}\",\n176\t        ], 500);\n177\t    }\n178\t}\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\tThe `/api/test-error` endpoint demonstrates manual exception capture. Use `?capture=true` to capture in PostHog, or `?capture=false` to skip tracking.\n182\t\n183\t\n184\t## Pages\n185\t\n186\t| Route | Component | PostHog Events |\n187\t|-------|-----------|----------------|\n188\t| `/` | Login | `user_logged_in` |\n189\t| `/register` | Register | `user_signed_up` |\n190\t| `/dashboard` | Dashboard | `dashboard_viewed`, feature flag checks |\n191\t| `/burrito` | BurritoTracker | `burrito_considered` |\n192\t| `/profile` | Profile | `profile_viewed` |\n193\t| `/logout` | (route) | `user_logged_out` |\n194\t\n195\t## Project Structure\n196\t\n197\t```\n198\tbasics/laravel/\n199\t├── app/\n200\t│   ├── Http/\n201\t│   │   ├── Controllers/\n202\t│   │   │   └── Api/\n203\t│   │   │       ├── BurritoController.php   # Burrito API endpoint\n204\t│   │   │       └── ErrorTestController.php # Error testing endpoint\n205\t│   │   └── Livewire/\n206\t│   │       ├── Auth/\n207\t│   │       │   ├── Login.php               # Login component\n208\t│   │       │   └── Register.php            # Registration component\n209\t│   │       ├── BurritoTracker.php          # Burrito tracker component\n210\t│   │       ├── Dashboard.php               # Dashboard with feature flags\n211\t│   │       └── Profile.php                 # User profile component\n212\t│   ├── Models/\n213\t│   │   └── User.php                        # User model with PostHog properties\n214\t│   └── Services/\n215\t│       └── PostHogService.php              # PostHog wrapper service\n216\t├── database/\n217\t│   ├── migrations/                         # Database migrations\n218\t│   └── seeders/\n219\t│       └── DatabaseSeeder.php              # Seeds admin user\n220\t├── resources/\n221\t│   └── views/\n222\t│       ├── components/\n223\t│       │   └── layouts/\n224\t│       │       ├── app.blade.php           # Authenticated layout\n225\t│       │       └── guest.blade.php         # Guest layout\n226\t│       ├── errors/\n227\t│       │   ├── 404.blade.php               # Not found page\n228\t│       │   └── 500.blade.php               # Server error page\n229\t│       └── livewire/\n230\t│           ├── auth/\n231\t│           │   ├── login.blade.php         # Login form\n232\t│           │   └── register.blade.php      # Registration form\n233\t│           ├── burrito-tracker.blade.php   # Burrito tracker UI\n234\t│           ├── dashboard.blade.php         # Dashboard UI\n235\t│           └── profile.blade.php           # Profile UI\n236\t├── routes/\n237\t│   ├── web.php                             # Web routes (auth, pages)\n238\t│   └── api.php                             # API routes\n239\t└── config/\n240\t    └── posthog.php                         # PostHog configuration\n241\t```\n242\t\n243\t## Development Commands\n244\t\n245\t```bash\n246\t# Start development server\n247\tphp artisan serve\n248\t\n249\t# Run migrations\n250\tphp artisan migrate\n251\t\n252\t# Seed database\n253\tphp artisan migrate:fresh --seed\n254\t\n255\t# Clear caches\n256\tphp artisan optimize:clear\n257\t```\n258\t---\n259\t\n260\t## .env.example\n261\t\n262\t```example\n263\tAPP_NAME=\"PostHog Laravel Example\"\n264\tAPP_ENV=local\n265\tAPP_KEY=\n266\tAPP_DEBUG=true\n267\tAPP_URL=http://localhost:8000\n268\t\n269\tDB_CONNECTION=sqlite\n270\t# DB_DATABASE will use default database/database.sqlite\n271\t\n272\tCACHE_DRIVER=file\n273\tCACHE_STORE=file\n274\t\n275\tSESSION_DRIVER=file\n276\tSESSION_LIFETIME=120\n277\t\n278\tPOSTHOG_PROJECT_TOKEN=your_posthog_project_token_here\n279\tPOSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com\n280\tPOSTHOG_DISABLED=false\n281\t\n282\t```\n283\t\n284\t---\n285\t\n286\t## app/Http/Controllers/Api/BurritoController.php\n287\t\n288\t```php\n289\t<?php\n290\t\n291\tnamespace App\\Http\\Controllers\\Api;\n292\t\n293\tuse App\\Http\\Controllers\\Controller;\n294\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n295\tuse Illuminate\\Http\\JsonResponse;\n296\tuse Illuminate\\Http\\Request;\n297\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n298\t\n299\tclass BurritoController extends Controller\n300\t{\n301\t    public function consider(Request $request, PostHogService $posthog): JsonResponse\n302\t    {\n303\t        $user = Auth::user();\n304\t\n305\t        // Increment session counter\n306\t        $burritoCount = session('burrito_count', 0) + 1;\n307\t        session(['burrito_count' => $burritoCount]);\n308\t\n309\t        // PostHog: Track event\n310\t        $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n311\t        $posthog->capture($user->email, 'burrito_considered', [\n312\t            'total_considerations' => $burritoCount,\n313\t        ]);\n314\t\n315\t        return response()->json([\n316\t            'success' => true,\n317\t            'count' => $burritoCount,\n318\t        ]);\n319\t    }\n320\t}\n321\t\n322\t```\n323\t\n324\t---\n325\t\n326\t## app/Http/Controllers/Api/ErrorTestController.php\n327\t\n328\t```php\n329\t<?php\n330\t\n331\tnamespace App\\Http\\Controllers\\Api;\n332\t\n333\tuse App\\Http\\Controllers\\Controller;\n334\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n335\tuse Illuminate\\Http\\JsonResponse;\n336\tuse Illuminate\\Http\\Request;\n337\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n338\t\n339\tclass ErrorTestController extends Controller\n340\t{\n341\t    public function test(Request $request, PostHogService $posthog): JsonResponse\n342\t    {\n343\t        $shouldCapture = $request->query('capture', 'true') === 'true';\n344\t        $user = Auth::user();\n345\t\n346\t        try {\n347\t            throw new \\Exception('Test exception from critical operation');\n348\t        } catch (\\Throwable $e) {\n349\t            if ($shouldCapture) {\n350\t                // Capture in PostHog\n351\t                $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n352\t                $eventId = $posthog->captureException($e, $user->email);\n353\t\n354\t                return response()->json([\n355\t                    'error' => 'Operation failed',\n356\t                    'error_id' => $eventId,\n357\t                    'message' => \"Error captured in PostHog. Reference ID: {$eventId}\",\n358\t                ], 500);\n359\t            }\n360\t\n361\t            return response()->json([\n362\t                'error' => $e->getMessage(),\n363\t            ], 500);\n364\t        }\n365\t    }\n366\t}\n367\t\n368\t```\n369\t\n370\t---\n371\t\n372\t## app/Http/Controllers/Controller.php\n373\t\n374\t```php\n375\t<?php\n376\t\n377\tnamespace App\\Http\\Controllers;\n378\t\n379\tabstract class Controller\n380\t{\n381\t    //\n382\t}\n383\t\n384\t```\n385\t\n386\t---\n387\t\n388\t## app/Http/Livewire/Auth/Login.php\n389\t\n390\t```php\n391\t<?php\n392\t\n393\tnamespace App\\Http\\Livewire\\Auth;\n394\t\n395\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n396\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n397\tuse Livewire\\Component;\n398\t\n399\tclass Login extends Component\n400\t{\n401\t    public string $email = '';\n402\t    public string $password = '';\n403\t    public bool $remember = false;\n404\t\n405\t    protected $rules = [\n406\t        'email' => 'required|email',\n407\t        'password' => 'required',\n408\t    ];\n409\t\n410\t    public function login(PostHogService $posthog)\n411\t    {\n412\t        $this->validate();\n413\t\n414\t        if (Auth::attempt(['email' => $this->email, 'password' => $this->password], $this->remember)) {\n415\t            $user = Auth::user();\n416\t\n417\t            // PostHog: Identify and track login\n418\t            $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n419\t            $posthog->capture($user->email, 'user_logged_in', [\n420\t                'login_method' => 'password',\n421\t            ]);\n422\t\n423\t            session()->regenerate();\n424\t\n425\t            return redirect()->intended(route('dashboard'));\n426\t        }\n427\t\n428\t        $this->addError('email', 'Invalid credentials');\n429\t    }\n430\t\n431\t    public function render()\n432\t    {\n433\t        return view('livewire.auth.login')\n434\t            ->layout('components.layouts.guest');\n435\t    }\n436\t}\n437\t\n438\t```\n439\t\n440\t---\n441\t\n442\t## app/Http/Livewire/Auth/Register.php\n443\t\n444\t```php\n445\t<?php\n446\t\n447\tnamespace App\\Http\\Livewire\\Auth;\n448\t\n449\tuse App\\Models\\User;\n450\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n451\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n452\tuse Livewire\\Component;\n453\t\n454\tclass Register extends Component\n455\t{\n456\t    public string $email = '';\n457\t    public string $password = '';\n458\t    public string $password_confirmation = '';\n459\t\n460\t    protected $rules = [\n461\t        'email' => 'required|email|unique:users,email',\n462\t        'password' => 'required|min:6|confirmed',\n463\t    ];\n464\t\n465\t    public function register(PostHogService $posthog)\n466\t    {\n467\t        $validated = $this->validate();\n468\t\n469\t        $user = User::create([\n470\t            'email' => $validated['email'],\n471\t            'password' => bcrypt($validated['password']),\n472\t            'is_staff' => false,\n473\t        ]);\n474\t\n475\t        // PostHog: Identify new user and track signup\n476\t        $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n477\t        $posthog->capture($user->email, 'user_signed_up', [\n478\t            'signup_method' => 'form',\n479\t        ]);\n480\t\n481\t        Auth::login($user);\n482\t\n483\t        session()->flash('success', 'Account created successfully!');\n484\t\n485\t        return redirect()->route('dashboard');\n486\t    }\n487\t\n488\t    public function render()\n489\t    {\n490\t        return view('livewire.auth.register')\n491\t            ->layout('components.layouts.guest');\n492\t    }\n493\t}\n494\t\n495\t```\n496\t\n497\t---\n498\t\n499\t## app/Http/Livewire/BurritoTracker.php\n500\t\n501\t```php\n502\t<?php\n503\t\n504\tnamespace App\\Http\\Livewire;\n505\t\n506\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n507\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n508\tuse Livewire\\Component;\n509\t\n510\tclass BurritoTracker extends Component\n511\t{\n512\t    public int $burritoCount = 0;\n513\t\n514\t    public function mount()\n515\t    {\n516\t        $this->burritoCount = session('burrito_count', 0);\n517\t    }\n518\t\n519\t    public function considerBurrito(PostHogService $posthog)\n520\t    {\n521\t        $this->burritoCount++;\n522\t        session(['burrito_count' => $this->burritoCount]);\n523\t\n524\t        // PostHog: Track burrito consideration\n525\t        $user = Auth::user();\n526\t        $posthog->identify($user->email, $user->getPostHogProperties());\n527\t        $posthog->capture($user->email, 'burrito_considered', [\n528\t            'total_considerations' => $this->burritoCount,\n529\t        ]);\n530\t\n531\t        $this->dispatch('burrito-considered');\n532\t    }\n533\t\n534\t    public function render()\n535\t    {\n536\t        return view('livewire.burrito-tracker')\n537\t            ->layout('components.layouts.app');\n538\t    }\n539\t}\n540\t\n541\t```\n542\t\n543\t---\n544\t\n545\t## app/Http/Livewire/Dashboard.php\n546\t\n547\t```php\n548\t<?php\n549\t\n550\tnamespace App\\Http\\Livewire;\n551\t\n552\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n553\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n554\tuse Livewire\\Component;\n555\t\n556\tclass Dashboard extends Component\n557\t{\n558\t    public bool $showNewFeature = false;\n559\t    public $featureConfig = null;\n560\t    public ?string $errorMessage = null;\n561\t    public ?string $successMessage = null;\n562\t\n563\t    public function mount(PostHogService $posthog)\n564\t    {\n565\t        $user = Auth::user();\n566\t\n567\t        // PostHog: Track dashboard view\n568\t        $posthog->capture($user->email, 'dashboard_viewed', [\n569\t            'is_staff' => $user->is_staff,\n570\t        ]);\n571\t\n572\t        // Check feature flag\n573\t        $this->showNewFeature = $posthog->isFeatureEnabled(\n574\t            'new-dashboard-feature',\n575\t            $user->email,\n576\t            $user->getPostHogProperties()\n577\t        ) ?? false;\n578\t\n579\t        // Get feature flag payload\n580\t        $this->featureConfig = $posthog->getFeatureFlagPayload(\n581\t            'new-dashboard-feature',\n582\t            $user->email\n583\t        );\n584\t    }\n585\t\n586\t    public function testErrorWithCapture(PostHogService $posthog)\n587\t    {\n588\t        $user = Auth::user();\n589\t\n590\t        try {\n591\t            // Simulate an error\n592\t            throw new \\Exception('This is a test error for PostHog tracking');\n593\t        } catch (\\Exception $e) {\n594\t            // Capture the exception in PostHog\n595\t            $errorId = $posthog->captureException($e, $user->email);\n596\t\n597\t            $this->successMessage = \"Error captured in PostHog! Error ID: {$errorId}\";\n598\t            $this->errorMessage = null;\n599\t        }\n600\t    }\n601\t\n602\t    public function testErrorWithoutCapture()\n603\t    {\n604\t        try {\n605\t            // Simulate an error without capturing\n606\t            throw new \\Exception('This error was NOT sent to PostHog');\n607\t        } catch (\\Exception $e) {\n608\t            $this->errorMessage = \"Error occurred but NOT captured in PostHog: \" . $e->getMessage();\n609\t            $this->successMessage = null;\n610\t        }\n611\t    }\n612\t\n613\t    public function render()\n614\t    {\n615\t        return view('livewire.dashboard')\n616\t            ->layout('components.layouts.app');\n617\t    }\n618\t}\n619\t\n620\t```\n621\t\n622\t---\n623\t\n624\t## app/Http/Livewire/Profile.php\n625\t\n626\t```php\n627\t<?php\n628\t\n629\tnamespace App\\Http\\Livewire;\n630\t\n631\tuse App\\Services\\PostHogService;\n632\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n633\tuse Livewire\\Component;\n634\t\n635\tclass Profile extends Component\n636\t{\n637\t    public ?string $errorMessage = null;\n638\t    public ?string $successMessage = null;\n639\t\n640\t    public function mount(PostHogService $posthog)\n641\t    {\n642\t        $user = Auth::user();\n643\t\n644\t        // PostHog: Track profile view\n645\t        $posthog->capture($user->email, 'profile_viewed');\n646\t    }\n647\t\n648\t    public function testErrorWithCapture(PostHogService $posthog)\n649\t    {\n650\t        $user = Auth::user();\n651\t\n652\t        try {\n653\t            // Simulate an error\n654\t            throw new \\Exception('This is a test error for PostHog tracking');\n655\t        } catch (\\Exception $e) {\n656\t            // Capture the exception in PostHog\n657\t            $errorId = $posthog->captureException($e, $user->email);\n658\t\n659\t            $this->successMessage = \"Error captured in PostHog! Error ID: {$errorId}\";\n660\t            $this->errorMessage = null;\n661\t        }\n662\t    }\n663\t\n664\t    public function testErrorWithoutCapture()\n665\t    {\n666\t        try {\n667\t            // Simulate an error without capturing\n668\t            throw new \\Exception('This error was NOT sent to PostHog');\n669\t        } catch (\\Exception $e) {\n670\t            $this->errorMessage = \"Error occurred but NOT captured in PostHog: \" . $e->getMessage();\n671\t            $this->successMessage = null;\n672\t        }\n673\t    }\n674\t\n675\t    public function render()\n676\t    {\n677\t        return view('livewire.profile')\n678\t            ->layout('components.layouts.app');\n679\t    }\n680\t}\n681\t\n682\t```\n683\t\n684\t---\n685\t\n686\t## app/Models/User.php\n687\t\n688\t```php\n689\t<?php\n690\t\n691\tnamespace App\\Models;\n692\t\n693\tuse Illuminate\\Database\\Eloquent\\Factories\\HasFactory;\n694\tuse Illuminate\\Foundation\\Auth\\User as Authenticatable;\n695\tuse Illuminate\\Notifications\\Notifiable;\n696\t\n697\tclass User extends Authenticatable\n698\t{\n699\t    use HasFactory, Notifiable;\n700\t\n701\t    protected $fillable = [\n702\t        'email',\n703\t        'password',\n704\t        'is_staff',\n705\t    ];\n706\t\n707\t    protected $hidden = [\n708\t        'password',\n709\t        'remember_token',\n710\t    ];\n711\t\n712\t    protected function casts(): array\n713\t    {\n714\t        return [\n715\t            'password' => 'hashed',\n716\t            'is_staff' => 'boolean',\n717\t        ];\n718\t    }\n719\t\n720\t    /**\n721\t     * Get PostHog person properties for this user.\n722\t     */\n723\t    public function getPostHogProperties(): array\n724\t    {\n725\t        return [\n726\t            'email' => $this->email,\n727\t            'is_staff' => $this->is_staff,\n728\t            'date_joined' => $this->created_at->toISOString(),\n729\t        ];\n730\t    }\n731\t}\n732\t\n733\t```\n734\t\n735\t---\n736\t\n737\t## app/Services/PostHogService.php\n738\t\n739\t```php\n740\t<?php\n741\t\n742\tnamespace App\\Services;\n743\t\n744\tuse PostHog\\PostHog;\n745\tuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n746\t\n747\tclass PostHogService\n748\t{\n749\t    protected static $initialized = false;\n750\t\n751\t    public function __construct()\n752\t    {\n753\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n754\t            return;\n755\t        }\n756\t\n757\t        // Initialize PostHog once\n758\t        if (!self::$initialized) {\n759\t            PostHog::init(\n760\t                config('posthog.api_key'),\n761\t                [\n762\t                    'host' => config('posthog.host'),\n763\t                    'debug' => config('posthog.debug'),\n764\t                ]\n765\t            );\n766\t            self::$initialized = true;\n767\t        }\n768\t    }\n769\t\n770\t    public function identify(string $distinctId, array $properties = []): void\n771\t    {\n772\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n773\t            return;\n774\t        }\n775\t\n776\t        PostHog::identify([\n777\t            'distinctId' => $distinctId,\n778\t            'properties' => $properties,\n779\t        ]);\n780\t    }\n781\t\n782\t    public function capture(string $distinctId, string $event, array $properties = []): void\n783\t    {\n784\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n785\t            return;\n786\t        }\n787\t\n788\t        PostHog::capture([\n789\t            'distinctId' => $distinctId,\n790\t            'event' => $event,\n791\t            'properties' => $properties,\n792\t        ]);\n793\t    }\n794\t\n795\t    public function captureException(\\Throwable $exception, ?string $distinctId = null): ?string\n796\t    {\n797\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n798\t            return null;\n799\t        }\n800\t\n801\t        $distinctId = $distinctId ?? Auth::user()?->email ?? 'anonymous';\n802\t\n803\t        $eventId = uniqid('error_', true);\n804\t\n805\t        PostHog::captureException($exception, $distinctId, [\n806\t            'error_id' => $eventId,\n807\t        ]);\n808\t\n809\t        return $eventId;\n810\t    }\n811\t\n812\t    public function isFeatureEnabled(string $key, string $distinctId, array $properties = []): ?bool\n813\t    {\n814\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n815\t            return false;\n816\t        }\n817\t\n818\t        return PostHog::isFeatureEnabled($key, $distinctId, $properties);\n819\t    }\n820\t\n821\t    public function getFeatureFlagPayload(string $key, string $distinctId)\n822\t    {\n823\t        if (config('posthog.disabled')) {\n824\t            return null;\n825\t        }\n826\t\n827\t        return PostHog::getFeatureFlagPayload($key, $distinctId);\n828\t    }\n829\t}\n830\t\n831\t```\n832\t\n833\t---\n834\t\n835\t## artisan\n836\t\n837\t```\n838\t#!/usr/bin/en